FLAVORS OF THE WORLD
Wherever we fly around the globe, we have the enviable job
of tasting and savoring the cuisines of the world. We invite you
to share our discoveries while traveling with us.
FILET TIPS BORDELAISE
The chefs of Bordeaux, a region known for gastronomy and
fine wines, are noted for their craftsmanship in blending wines
with classical sauces. These methods are used to create this
dish which combines choice filet tips, shallots, mushrooms, and
herbs, all simmered in a Bordeaux wine flavored Beef Stock.
Accompanied by spiced rice and honey glazed carrots.
ROAST PORK LOIN PAKIPIKA
Pronounced PAH KEE PEE KAH, this entree was found in the
island paradise of Hawaii. Generous slices of roast pork are
served in their natural juices that have been sharpened with
honey, ginger and a hint of soy sauce. The moist apple stuffing,
fruit garnishes, and green beans with chopped peanuts are the
perfect complement.
BAKED CHICKEN, PLANTATION STYLE
From the deep South comes this unusual version of Southern
fried chicken. Our cooks take a boneless Spring chicken breast,
dip it in a cream batter and roll it in buttery bread crumbs
mixed with fresh herbs and spices. Baked until golden brown,
we serve it with glazed yams and green peas with pimento.
